How it works:
1. "Settings" tab - choose what to fill (FBU or projects) 2. Fill "Source data" tab. From excel ("Upload from excel" button) or manually ("Add" or "Delete" buttons) or by db request ("Generate" button) 3. Excel file format: first row - header. Number for rows (Login, role, etc.) you can check or edit on "Settings" tab 4. Go to required tab (i.e. ED) 5. Press "Validate" button. You will see existing access or possible errors In case of any error - row won't be updated 6. Optional. SOD check. You can check in AllRights system. 7. You can add or delete validated access
For adding - row with data "access" or "principal and access" will be processed For deleting - row with data "exists" will be processed All other data will be skipped
8. "FBU Manager" tab. Main steps 1 - 4. To add manager you can use role names: for FBU manager : "manager" or "1" for FBU manager delegated : "managerdelegated" or "2"
9. "Projects Data" tab. Please choose Access type = Project (Settings tab) Main steps 1 - 4. To add project role you can use names: SE or Billing Project Manager: "PM" or "projectmanager" SE or Billing Account Manager: "AM" or "accountmanager" Billing OS Responsible: "osresponsible"
